--- Part 2: The β₁=3 gap at n=5 ---
  β₁=3 would need (t₃,d₅) with t₃+d₅=3:
    (3,0): t₃=3 forces d₅≥1 (HYP-1022 — 3 directed 3-cycles force a 5-cycle)
    (2,1): d₅=1 means one 5-set has exactly 1 directed Ham cycle
    (1,2): d₅=2 means a 5-set has 2 directed Ham cycles
    (0,3): d₅=3 means a 5-set has 3 directed Ham cycles

  Do (2,1), (1,2), (0,3) exist?
    (2,1): DOES NOT EXIST (0 tournaments)
    (1,2): DOES NOT EXIST (0 tournaments)
    (0,3): DOES NOT EXIST (0 tournaments)
    (3,0): DOES NOT EXIST (0 tournaments)

