--- Part 5: Why β₁+2β₂ skips 10 ---
  At n=6 with no 7-cycles (n<7):
  β₁ = t₃ + d₅
  β₂ = Σ_{disjoint (S,T)} d(S)·d(T)

  For β₁+2β₂=10 we need:
  Case β₂=0: β₁=10, so t₃+d₅=10. Max t₃ at n=6 is 10.
  Case β₂=1: β₁=8, so t₃+d₅=8, plus exactly 1 disjoint weighted pair
  etc.

  But t₃+d₅=10 with β₂=0 means all cycle vertex sets intersect.
  At t₃=10 (max), does d₅=0 and β₂=0 hold?

  Scanning all n=6 tournaments with β₁+2β₂ in [8,12]:
  (If no FOUND message, β₁+2β₂=10 is impossible at n=6)
